@startuml
title AWS IoT Device Simulator - Deployment and Connectivity Flow

actor User
participant "CloudFormation" as CF
participant "Custom Resource\nLambda" as CRL
participant "S3 Bucket" as S3
participant "Microservices\nLambda" as MSL
participant "DynamoDB" as DB
participant "Step Functions" as SF
participant "Simulator\nLambda" as SIM
participant "AWS IoT Core" as IOT
participant "Device Engine" as ENG

== Deployment Phase ==
User -> CF: Deploy CloudFormation Stack
activate CF

CF -> CRL: Create Custom Resource
activate CRL
CRL -> CRL: Generate UUID
CRL -> S3: Copy Assets to S3
activate S3
S3 --> CRL: Assets Copied
deactivate S3
CRL -> IOT: Create IoT Policy
activate IOT
IOT --> CRL: Policy Created
deactivate IOT
CRL --> CF: Custom Resource Complete
deactivate CRL

CF -> DB: Create DynamoDB Tables
activate DB
DB --> CF: Tables Created
deactivate DB

CF -> MSL: Deploy Microservices Lambda
activate MSL
MSL --> CF: Lambda Deployed
deactivate MSL

CF -> SF: Create Step Functions State Machine
activate SF
SF --> CF: State Machine Created
deactivate SF

CF -> SIM: Deploy Simulator Lambda
activate SIM
SIM --> CF: Lambda Deployed
deactivate SIM

CF --> User: Stack Deployment Complete
deactivate CF

== Device Type Configuration ==
User -> MSL: Create Device Type (API Request)
activate MSL
MSL -> DB: Store Device Type Definition
activate DB
DB --> MSL: Device Type Stored
deactivate DB
MSL --> User: Device Type Created
deactivate MSL

== Simulation Initialization ==
User -> MSL: Create Simulation (API Request)
activate MSL
MSL -> DB: Store Simulation Configuration
activate DB
DB --> MSL: Simulation Stored
deactivate DB
MSL -> SF: Start Simulation Execution
activate SF
MSL --> User: Simulation Created
deactivate MSL

== Simulation Execution & Connectivity ==
SF -> SIM: Invoke Simulator Lambda
activate SIM
SIM -> DB: Retrieve Device Type & Simulation Config
activate DB
DB --> SIM: Configuration Data
deactivate DB

SIM -> ENG: Initialize Device Engine
activate ENG
ENG -> ENG: Create Device Instances (Factory Pattern)
ENG --> SIM: Devices Initialized
deactivate ENG

loop For Each Simulated Device
    SIM -> SIM: Generate Data (Strategy Pattern)
    SIM -> IOT: Publish MQTT Message
    activate IOT
    IOT --> SIM: Message Accepted
    deactivate IOT
end

SIM -> SIM: Check Simulation Duration
alt Simulation Complete
    SIM --> SF: Execution Complete
    deactivate SIM
else Continue Simulation
    SF -> SIM: Re-invoke Simulator Lambda
    activate SIM
    SIM --> SF: Execution Continues
    deactivate SIM
end
deactivate SF

== IoT Data Flow ==
IOT -> IOT: Route Messages to AWS Services
IOT --> User: Data Available for Testing/Analysis

== Simulation Management ==
User -> MSL: Stop Simulation (API Request)
activate MSL
MSL -> SF: Stop State Machine Execution
activate SF
SF -> SIM: Cancel Execution
activate SIM
SIM --> SF: Stopped
deactivate SIM
SF --> MSL: Execution Stopped
deactivate SF
MSL -> DB: Update Simulation Status
activate DB
DB --> MSL: Status Updated
deactivate DB
MSL --> User: Simulation Stopped
deactivate MSL

== Cleanup Phase ==
User -> CF: Delete CloudFormation Stack
activate CF
CF -> CRL: Delete Custom Resource
activate CRL
CRL -> IOT: Detach IoT Policy
activate IOT
IOT --> CRL: Policy Detached
deactivate IOT
CRL --> CF: Cleanup Complete
deactivate CRL
CF -> DB: Delete DynamoDB Tables
activate DB
DB --> CF: Tables Deleted
deactivate DB
CF -> S3: Delete S3 Bucket Contents
activate S3
S3 --> CF: Contents Deleted
deactivate S3
CF --> User: Stack Deleted
deactivate CF

@enduml
